Place the @Diced Irish Chicken Breast{260%g} in a #bowl{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and
equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Add the @Soy Sauce{1%sachet}, toss to coat, then leave aside to marinate.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal
due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

Trim the @Cucumber{1}(quartered lengthways then chopped widthways into small pieces),
quarter lengthways then chop widthways into small pieces.

Add the cucumber to a bowl along with the @Tahini{2%sachets} and @Yoghurt{75%g}.
Season to taste with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}.

Peel and grate the @Garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @Carrot{1}
then coarsely grate (no need to peel).

Halve the @Cherry Tomatoes{125%g}.

Finely chop the @Parsley{5%g}(stalks and all).

Zest and quarter the @Lemon{1}.

Add the @Couscous{100%g}, lemon zest and @Salt{¼%tsp} (double for 4p) to a #medium
bowl{}.

Pour in @Water{200%ml}(boiling) (500ml for 4p).

Give it a stir, cover with a #plate{} or #cling film{} and leave aside for
~{10%minutes} (or until ready to serve).

Once ready, stir the grated carrot through the couscous. Season to taste with salt
and pepper.

Meanwhile, mix a drizzle of @Oil{to taste} with the juice of half the lemon wedges
in a #large bowl{}.

Add the @Dried Chilli Flakes{1%sachet} (use less if you don't like spice), garlic
and chopped parsley.

Stir to combine and season to taste with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Use a blender if you'd like a smoother consistency.

Place a #large pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once the oil is hot, add the chicken and season with salt and pepper.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.
IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When everything's ready, fluff up the couscous with a #fork{} and divide between
#bowls{}.

Top with tomatoes and cooling cucumber.

Finish with the diced chicken and a drizzle of the chimichurri sauce.

Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side for squeezing over.